[♪ tense music playing]

276
00:19:04,540 --> 00:19:06,834
"Did it"? Did what?

277
00:19:07,501 --> 00:19:09,378
I mean, we became one.

278
00:19:09,462 --> 00:19:11,589
Kasuga and I.

279
00:19:12,173 --> 00:19:13,716
So what?

280
00:19:13,799 --> 00:19:16,177
Do what you want.

281
00:19:16,260 --> 00:19:17,970
I don't care.

282
00:19:19,513 --> 00:19:21,140
You see,

283
00:19:22,308 --> 00:19:24,685
Kasuga was only using you
as an escape, Nakamura.

284
00:19:25,144 --> 00:19:26,854
He was taking the easy way out.

285
00:19:28,105 --> 00:19:30,024
But I've accepted him for who he is,

286
00:19:30,107 --> 00:19:32,485
and together, we're taking steps forward.

287
00:19:33,694 --> 00:19:36,113
So, he no longer needs you, Nakamura.

288
00:19:36,197 --> 00:19:39,283
Tell me, how do you feel right now?

289
00:19:39,950 --> 00:19:42,161
Kasuga's been taken from you,

290
00:19:42,244 --> 00:19:44,997
and everything's up in flames.
How do you feel right now?

291
00:19:45,623 --> 00:19:47,082
So dumb.

292
00:19:47,166 --> 00:19:48,959
It's really so dumb.

293
00:19:54,757 --> 00:19:56,884
Ain't nothin' dumb about it!

294
00:19:57,468 --> 00:20:01,764
You've always made fun of me,
looking down on me this whole time!

295
00:20:06,435 --> 00:20:07,686
[♪ music fades]

296
00:20:12,817 --> 00:20:15,361
-[siren baring]
-What the hell?

297
00:20:15,444 --> 00:20:17,154
Let go of me!

298
00:20:17,655 --> 00:20:19,698
[sobbing] Say you're mad at me!

299
00:20:19,782 --> 00:20:24,203
You're resentful
that I stole Kasuga from you, aren't you?

300
00:20:24,745 --> 00:20:27,540
You're frustrated! Admit it!

301
00:20:27,623 --> 00:20:30,251
[sobs] Damn it.

302
00:20:31,043 --> 00:20:32,378
[♪ somber music playing]

303
00:20:32,461 --> 00:20:34,129
Damn it!

304
00:20:37,842 --> 00:20:39,593
Why... [sniffles]

305
00:20:41,637 --> 00:20:45,349
Why can't I be you, Nakamura?
STYLE
::cue()

306
00:20:54,108 --> 00:20:56,068
There, you finally spat it out.

307
00:20:57,528 --> 00:20:58,696
Still...

308
00:20:58,779 --> 00:21:02,241
You're more rotten inside than a fly.

309
00:21:03,367 --> 00:21:04,827
You will never understand me,

310
00:21:05,578 --> 00:21:07,997
and I'd rather die
than let you think you could.

311
00:21:14,962 --> 00:21:16,755
[siren wailing]

312
00:21:21,969 --> 00:21:23,762
[indistinct chatter over radio]

313
00:21:29,143 --> 00:21:31,228
[Takao] Let's start over again.

314
00:21:31,312 --> 00:21:34,189
We still have two days until the festival.

315
00:21:35,316 --> 00:21:36,817
[Sawa] Kasuga,

316
00:21:38,819 --> 00:21:41,697
where does this road lead to?

317
00:21:44,283 --> 00:21:46,327
At the end of this road, everything's...

318
00:21:47,411 --> 00:21:48,537
dead.

319
00:21:50,331 --> 00:21:51,582
I...

320
00:21:52,333 --> 00:21:53,876
don't want to die.

321
00:21:55,794 --> 00:21:56,795
Then...

322
00:21:56,879 --> 00:21:58,380
what can I do?

323
00:21:58,464 --> 00:22:00,215
Where should we go?

324
00:22:07,848 --> 00:22:09,266
I'll think of something.

325
00:22:10,601 --> 00:22:12,019
I promise I'll find it!

326
00:22:12,102 --> 00:22:13,437
So...

327
00:22:14,396 --> 00:22:15,439
So, please...

328
00:22:25,866 --> 00:22:27,701
[♪ somber music playing]

329
00:22:32,122 --> 00:22:33,123
[Nanako] Excuse me.

330
00:22:33,207 --> 00:22:35,334
Yes? How may I help you?

331
00:22:36,877 --> 00:22:38,963
That fire on the riverbank last night...

332
00:22:39,046 --> 00:22:40,047
MASTER PLAN

333
00:22:42,758 --> 00:22:45,094
I'm the one that set it.

334
00:22:48,472 --> 00:22:50,808
TO BE CONTINUED

335
00:22:50,891 --> 00:22:53,978
[♪ closing theme music playing]

336
00:23:47,948 --> 00:23:48,991
ON THE NEXT EPISODE

337
00:23:49,074 --> 00:23:52,619
[narrator] Saeki strips Kasuga
and Nakamura of any safe space they had.

338
00:23:52,703 --> 00:23:55,080
Where will the two head to together?

339
00:23:55,164 --> 00:23:57,541
Next, on episode seven,

340
00:23:57,624 --> 00:24:01,045
Nakamura takes Kasuga
and sets out to reach "the other side".

341
00:24:01,128 --> 00:24:02,880
Translated by Yuka Kristi

